HEADWORD: Well-intentioned
<hw>Well`-in*ten"tioned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
upright intentions or honorable purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dutchmen who had sold themselves to France, as the
<qex>wellintentioned</qex> party.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

